<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old man who admitted killing his mistress was sentenced Thursday to 
26 years to life in prison. 
</P>
<P>
Filomeno Huerta, 24, was convicted of murder Jan. 11 in the Sept. 5, 1989, 
slaying of Silvia Flores, 23, also from Escondido. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Superior Court Judge William Kennedy also fined Huerta $200. 
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Probation Department, Huerta said he killed the woman 
because "anger overcame me." He denied planning to kill Flores earlier. 
</P>
<P>
She was stabbed and had her head smashed against a concrete block. Her badly 
decomposed body was found Sept. 16 in a drainage ditch off San Pasqual Road 
near the San Diego Wild Animal Park. 
</P>
<P>
Huerta said he believed that Flores had told his wife about their affair, 
causing his wife to go back to Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
