<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A new attorney and a new trial date were granted Thursday to Roger Sing Ip, 
accused of killing a 15-year-old boy following a traffic dispute. 
</P>
<P>
Ip, 33, of Spring Valley is charged with murdering Kurt Von Yokes on July 10 in 
Pacific Beach after teen-agers in the car in which Yokes was a passenger yelled 
at Ip about his driving. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Superior Court Judge William Howatt Jr. vacated the current trial 
date of March 5 and reset it for June 15. 
</P>
<P>
Attorney Elisabeth Semel was relieved of the case and attorney John Fletcher 
was named to replace her. 
</P>
<P>
Semel said she cannot discuss why the change in attorneys was made, but 
acknowledged she had preferred to stay on the case. 
</P>
<P>
Ip remains in county jail in lieu of $1 million bail. 
</P>
