<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A van overturned Thursday while on a ramp from Interstate 5 to Interstate 8 and 
ended up in an embankment, authorities said. The driver was not seriously 
injured. 
</P>
<P>
California Highway Patrol Officer Joe Wolf said the driver, Rodney Scott 
McMillan, was headed north on I-5 and was about to enter I-8 westbound when he 
suddenly veered to the right in an attempt to get on the I-8 eastbound ramp. 
McMillan lost control of the van, which then went over the side of the road and 
hit a barrier between the freeway and a restaurant in the 4300 block of Pacific 
Highway, Wolf said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred about 3 p.m. McMillan was taken to UCSD Medical Center, 
where he was treated for minor injuries. 
</P>
