</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Loyola Marymount women's basketball team has a shot at first place when it 
plays host to the University of San Francisco at 7:30 tonight and St. Mary's at 
7:30 Saturday. USF and St. Mary's enter the weekend tied for first in the West 
Coast Conference at 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
The Lions are a game and a half behind at 5-3 (12-10 overall). The Lions upset 
USF in San Francisco last weekend to create the first-place tie. 
</P>
<P>
