<HEADLINE>
<P>
BISHOP'S GIRL SETS SOCCER SCORING MARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore striker Carmel Murphy of Bishop's School has set a girls' section 
soccer record for goals in a season with 55. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy scored two goals Wednesday in Bishop's 4-1 City Central League victory 
over Madison and two more Thursday in a 6-1 victory over Crawford. The previous 
record was 51, set by Laurie Tharp of Mission Bay in 1985. 
</P>
<P>
"(Murphy's) fiercely competitive and just hates to lose," said Ren Marquette, 
Bishop's athletic director. "She's fast and has great skills." 
</P>
<P>
Bishops (18-0-2) was ranked seventh in the most recent section coaches' 
rankings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
