<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colgate-Palmolive Co.: The consumer products maker reported that 1989 net 
income fell 12% from a year ago, to $280 million, on revenue of $5 billion, up 
6%. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth quarter, the New York company's profit fell to $62.5 million 
from $126.7 million, on revenue of $1.3 billion, up 6% from the 1988 period. 
The firm said 1988 full-year and fourth-quarter results included a gain from 
the sale of its Kendall health-care unit and a charge related to Hill's Pet 
Products. Excluding those, Colgate-Palmolive said, net income rose 19% for the 
year and 43% for the quarter. 
</P>
