<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tenneco Inc.: The Houston-based company said 1989 net income was $584 million, 
down from $822 million in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
The company noted that 1988 income reflected $823 million from discontinued 
operations, primarily profit on the sale of Tenneco Oil Co. Without the 
one-time gain, the company posted a $1-million loss from continuing operations 
in 1988. Revenue was $14.1 billion for 1989, compared to $13.2 billion for 
1988. The significant improvement in 1989 results was led by the strong 
performance in the farm and construction equipment business and improvements in 
natural gas pipeline operations, the company said. 
</P>
