</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOTHESLINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYLOU LUTHER, Luther is a Times syndicated writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Q: I will be getting married in March at a simple ceremony with only close 
friends and immediate family in attendance. As this will be a second wedding 
for me, I was thinking of wearing a suit. 
</P>
<P>
What do you recommend for someone 36, 5'6", Size 10? -- S.E. 
</P>
<P>
A: How about a lace jacket with a chiffon skirt, as illustrated here? This 
romantic suit is by Susan Lane, bridal gown designer and owner of Country 
Elegance, who suggests that you buy the jacket in ivory lace over rose-beige 
satin and the skirt in blush pink, a shade lighter than rose-beige. Lane says 
that blush pink is the No. 1 color for all wedding gowns sold at her shop, 
replacing white and antique ivory. She believes it's especially appropriate for 
what she calls encore brides. This suit, priced at $450, comes in Sizes 6-16 at 
Country Elegance, 7375 Greenbush Ave., North Hollywood, Calif. 91605. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, Lace jacket with a chiffon skirt / FERNANDO FLORES 
</P>
