<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Idol Update: Rock star Billy Idol is scheduled for additional surgery Saturday 
to repair his right leg, severely broken in a Tuesday motorcycle accident in 
Hollywood, his publicist said. However, Chrysalis Records has said it will go 
ahead with the scheduled April 17 release of Idol's just completed "Charmed 
Life" album, with the single "Cradle of Love" to be issued April 10, though a 
planned 1990 concert tour is in doubt. Meanwhile, director Oliver Stone 
released a statement Thursday that he still wants Idol to co-star in his film 
biography of the late Jim Morrison, scheduled to begin shooting in early March, 
but may have to recast if Idol's recovery takes too long. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
