<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; 
</P>
<P>
CITY TO INSTALL TWO RADAR SPEED SIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Signs that automatically display the speeds of passing drivers and the speed 
limit will be installed at two sites in the city. 
</P>
<P>
The movable radar signs, which are expected to be up for about six weeks, will 
be used in connection with police surveillance to decrease drivers' speeds. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council this week agreed to spend $14,000 for the equipment. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Irwin M. Fried said when he once passed such a sign, "the first 
thing I did was check my speed. The second thing I did was check the speed 
limit on the street. The third thing I did was check to see if there were any 
police cars around, and the fourth thing I did was I definitely slowed down." 
</P>
<P>
The council has not yet decided where the trailers will be placed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
