<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outfielder Danny Tartabull reached agreement with the Kansas City Royals on a 
one-year contract for $1.65 million, avoiding an arbitration hearing. 
</P>
<P>
Tartabull, a holdout in spring training last year, had sought $1.735 million. 
The Royals had offered $1.285 million. The right fielder made $1.035 million 
last year. 
</P>
<P>
Tartabull hit .268 with 18 home runs and 62 RBIs in 133 games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
