<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUNSET LEAGUE GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
A RECORD PERFORMANCE FOR FISCHER; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL: EDISON GUARD BREAKS RECORDS FOR POINTS AND THREE-POINTERS 
AND TIES ANOTHER IN VICTORY OVER WESTMINSTER. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN Fountain Valley 51, Huntington Beach 32 -- Julie Workman scored 
13 and Jennifer Barbaro added 11 for Fountain Valley, which led, 24-13, at the 
half. Fountain Valley is 17-9, 6-4. Jana Davis scored 16 and Dana Jahr added 12 
for Huntington Beac 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Debbie Fischer scored a school-record 49 points, broke the Southern Section 
records for career and season three-pointers and tied her single-game Southern 
Section record with 10 three-point baskets to lead Edison High School to a 
88-33 victory over Westminster in a Sunset League girls' basketball game 
Thursday at Edison. 
</P>
<P>
Fischer's 10 three-pointers tied the record she set in December against Corona. 
</P>
<P>
She also broke her school single-game record of 40 points. 
</P>
<P>
Fischer has 92 three-pointers this season, which broke the record of 66 set by 
Linda Watson of Lynwood last season. Fischer has 100 career three-pointers, 
which broke the record of 79 set by Judy Gilliam of Glendora in 1987-88. 
</P>
<P>
"I guess somewhere somebody had 12 three-pointers in a game and it wasn't 
reported, so we wanted Debbie to have a chance (to be the undisputed 
record-holder)," Edison coach Philip Abraham said. "In third quarter, I said to 
my assistant coaches . . . let her go for it (12). I said to her, 'Debbie you 
have eight three pointers" because she didn't know." 
</P>
<P>
"The third quarter was really great for me. After I hit two (three-pointers) I 
said, 'Give me the ball!' " Fischer said. ARA NAJARIANFountain Valley 51, 
Huntington Beach 32 -- Julie Workman scored 13 and Jennifer Barbaro added 11 
for Fountain Valley, which led, 24-13, at the half. Fountain Valley is 17-9, 
6-4. Jana Davis scored 16 and Dana Jahr added 12 for Huntington Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
