<TEXT>
<P>
Marshall Field, Saks Up for Sale: Two of the classiest names in retailing, 
Marshall Field and Saks Fifth Avenue, were placed on the auction block by BAT 
Industries PLC, which hopes to fetch $1 billion for each of the chains. 
Chicago-based Marshall Field has 24 stores and New York-based Saks has 46. BAT, 
the London-based conglomerate, is trying to fend off the unwanted advances of 
corporate raider Sir James Goldsmith. 
