<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Genentech Shareholders File Suit: Four Genentech Inc. shareholders have filed 
suit in Delaware Chancery Court to block the sale of a 60% stake in the firm to 
Roche Holding Co., according to Federal Filings Inc. The report said the 
holders contend that the sale of new shares to Roche would severely dilute the 
holdings of current holders. They also claim that the $2.1-billion deal is a 
change of control of the company, which obligates the Genentech board to 
conduct an auction. The South San Francisco-based biotechnology concern said it 
had not seen the suit. 
</P>
