<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFI WRITERS WORKSHOP SEEKING MINORITY SCRIPTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The American Film Institute Alumni Assn. Writers Workshop is seeking script 
submissions from minority screenwriters in Los Angeles for its newly 
established Ethnic Minority Screenwriters Development Program. 
</P>
<P>
Five winners will be chosen to receive a $500 scholarship and a personal 
critique of their work from an industry expert. 
</P>
<P>
The program was created in response to a report by the Writer's Guild of 
America West which stated that only 2% of writers employed each year are 
minorities. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for submissions is March 10. The submission fee is $25. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 559-4512. 
</P>
</TEXT>
