<P>
MALAYSIA CANCELS LATOYA SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Valentine's Day concert by LaToya Jackson has been canceled because her 
presence would violate the values of Malaysian culture, the Culture and Tourism 
Ministry said today. 
</P>
<P>
The department secretary, Mukhtar Abdullah, said Jackson, who posed nude in 
Playboy magazine last year, did not meet some of the conditions imposed by the 
government on foreign artists performing in Malaysia. He did not say what these 
conditions were. 
</P>
<P>
He said he was surprised the promoter, Genesis Promotions, went ahead through 
newspapers and television ads without getting the ministry's approval. 
</P>
