<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
NACHOS UPSTAGE SUPERSTARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harrison Ford, Chevy Chase and Sean Connery are here at the annual convention 
of theater owners, but the people at Proctor Cos. swear the biggest star around 
is Proctor's new nacho cheese dispenser. 
</P>
<P>
More than 80% of a theater's profits are generated at the concession stand, and 
many of the 3,000 executives gathered for the National Assn. of Theater Owners 
ShoWest trade meeting are seeking every opportunity to squeeze the snack bar 
for a few more dollars. 
</P>
<P>
Given that motivation, Hollywood superstars, previews of upcoming attractions 
and endless cocktail parties take a back seat to such inventions as the $450 
Hot Topper, which Proctor says can squirt out melted nacho cheese, fudge or 
butter without mess and little waste. 
</P>
<P>
And what food innovation will you see soon at a theater near you? Perhaps iced 
cappuccino, which comes in three flavors -- chocolate, amaretto and classic -- 
and will sell for about $1.50. 
</P>
</TEXT>
